Invasive Species Management

OHI+ Palmyra 2020 Assessment

Compiled on Thu Aug 20 11:18:12 2020 by orofino

Summary

Regulatory resilience is meant to describes the institutional measures (e.g., rules, regulations, and laws) designed to address ecological pressures. This script calculates resilience from the management of invasive species on Palmyra Atoll.

Data

Data to inform the preparation of this layer comes from the Existing Non-Native Species Laws, Policies, Protocols section of the 2010 Palmyra Biosecurity Plan.

Citation: Hathaway, S.A. and Fisher, R.N. (2010). Biosecurity Plan for Palmyra Atoll: U.S. Geological Survey Open-File Report 2010-1097, 80p.
Available here

Setup

library(tidyverse)
library(here)

# Source and set file paths
source(here('src/R/common.R'))

dir_res   <- '~/github/pal-prep/prep/resilience/ecological/invasive_species/v2020'

Methods

Resilience Score

A resilience layer is created for management of invasive species based on three criteria:

  • Is there a management plan in place?
  • Is there monitoring and assessment?
  • Is the management plan effective?

A yes will be assigned a value of 1, in-development will be assigned a value of 0.5, a no will be assigned a value of 0. The Palmyra Atoll Biosecurity Plan established in 2010 details a series of adaptive management plans designed to achieve TNCs mission toward the protection and enhancement of native wildlife and habitat. Since the established of the plan, major actions to remove priority species, such as invasive rats (Rattus rattus) have been undertaken. Monitoring for invasive species continues to take place and there are additional plans to continue removal of other high priority species like coconut palm (Cocos nucifera).

Category Response Score
Management Plan? Yes 1
Monitoring? Yes 1
Effective? Yes 1 
years <- 2014:2020

sp_mgmt <- data.frame(
  region_id = rep(1, length(years)),
  year = years,
  resilience_score = rep(1, length(years))
)

# Save to output folder
write_csv(sp_mgmt, file.path(dir_res, "output/sp_mgmt.csv"))
